 Tsomo - Justice was finally served when the Tsomo Regional Magistrate’s Court sentenced a 22-year-old man, Sanele Mpumlwana, to undergo 12 years imprisonment for rape. "The accused was sentenced on Thursday at the Tsomo Regional Magistrate's Court," said police spokesperson, Capt Jackson Manatha. "It is alleged that an 18-year-old woman was from Njekeni Locality to Sqithini Locality at Xilinxa Village, Ngqamakhwe, on 26 March 2018, at about 15h45. "While she was crossing the river, she came across the accused, who was armed with a knife." Capt Manatha said that the accused person threatened the victim with his knife and raped her. "The victim identified the accused as they are from the same village.  A case of rape was registered at Ngqamakhwe Police Station." The case was handed over to Butterworth Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit (FCS), who later traced and arrested Mpumlwana. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 